metadata.name: Last Rose
metadata.description:
There is a light behind your eyes that will never go out.

Your body may weaken with the passing years, but your soul burns with a secret flame, brighter than an evening star.

As children, we live in awe of everything. The bright blue sky, the sound of crashing waves. How can such beauty be killed? A defect in our code, a mislabeled bottle of cosmic magic?

If life is a struggle between love and death, then choose love until your very last sound.

And may your last rose be as red as the first.
